(15, 1, '2014-04-29 15:12:06', '2014-04-29 15:12:06', 'John L. Thompson, born Mar. 15, 1890, died Jan. 1, 1950. Married Edith Fetterly, school teacher, born July 4, 1885, died July 31, 1955. She was crippled with arthritis in her later years and died at the home of her son, Lorne. John had been a cheese maker, alcohol salesman, hunter, carpenter, etc., and was separated from his wife for the last years of their marriage. (Three children from another relationship. (died as Allan Bailey -buried in Midland)\r\n\r\nJohn moved to Midland and changed his name to Allen Bailey. He and Mrs. Bailey had four children. Mrs. Bailey was born in 1901 and died Nov. 23, 1990. John died and is buried in the Midland cemetery as Allen Bailey.', 'John L. Thompson', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'john-l-thompson', '', '', '2014-04-29 15:59:48', '2014-04-29 15:59:48', '', 0, 'http://thompsons.plansmash.com/tree/?p=15', 0, 'post', '', 0),
