(117, 1, '2010-12-31 14:20:02', '2010-12-31 19:20:02', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Shendah Lyons</li>\r\n	<li>Chris Chartrand</li>\r\n	<li>Mary Hyatt</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNigel was away from our home in Montreal with Shawn to get in his Nintendo (DS) fixed\r\n\r\nChris Chartrand appeared at Shendah and Shawn door in Montreal. Chris asked for Shawn. Shendah told him he was not home. Chris asked if Shendah knew when he would be home. Shendah asked if Mary was with him. Chris said she was waiting in the car. Chris said he did not know what to do at this point. Shendah told him he was there to support Mary. Shendah stated that she did not want any violence. Chris exclaimed in surprise that he was not at all here for that. He said that he needed to deliver court order papers. Shendah asked him to go get Mary and she could come up but he was not permitted in the apartment. Chris said he understood. Chris went and got Mary.\r\n\r\nShendah phoned Shawn to inform him that Mary and Chris were here. Shawn said he was coming right home.  Mary came to the door with Chris and asked when Shawn would be home. Shendah told her that she had just called him. Mary asked if she could give the court order to Shendah and Shendah refused to take it because she is not the recipient. Mary told Shendah that the court office said that she could mail it and Shendah told her to wait for Shawn.\r\n\r\nShendah invited Mary in her home and notified Mary that she did not want any violence in her home. Mary agreed. Shendah changed her mind about Chris being in the house and allowed him to come in. Shendah, Chris and Mary sat in the kitchen and talked about the incident.\r\n\r\nAt that time, Chris did not talk once during the conversation. Shendah exclaimed how sorry she was that this was going on and told her genuine concerns about Nigel’s welfare. At the point Mary brought up the court order and said that in no way were those allegations a reason for her not to have her son. Shendah acknowledged that she heard her. Mary denied the weight loss. She appeared sober and fidgety most likely related to nerves of the situation. Chris appeared to have glassy eyes but very quiet when in Mary’s presence. Mary said that she tried to deal with this situation years ago with the lawyers but blamed Shawn for procrastinating. She claimed that because of him she received a 3000$ lawyer bill (to which it was known at the time her father was paying) Shendah responded and said that Shawn had received the same thing. Shendah not believing her about Shawn ‘s “procrastination” had been about not wanting Mary to have 100% decision making power and having a joint custody affair to which Mary did not agree to.  Knowing far more about the situation that Mary suspected just acknowledged that she heard her. Shendah then told her that both of them are at fault for not getting this done in the first place. Shendah also stated that as parents they need to learn to communicate and that both of them are flat out stupid for not doing so. Mary did not respond.\r\n\r\nShendah stated that Mary needed to find a job. Mary claimed at this point she did not want to take a job that she was over qualified for and that because every time she tries Nigel gets in trouble at school and she did not specify. She said that she could not take a job on evenings and weekends because she needs to take care of Nigel. To which Shendah responded that was true. Shendah offered that maybe she could move to Montreal and Shendah would help her find a job and even translate her CV. To that Mary responded that her French was not good enough. To that Shendah responded that if it was better than Shawn’s, a statement she had heard many times before, then her French would be fine. Shendah also stated that she works in the psychiatric hospital system and she could get Nigel an appointment at the Douglas to help with his supposed undiagnosed ADHD problem. Shendah told her that the Douglas has some the best psychiatrist in the world.\r\n\r\nMary also said that Nigel would have to go to school in French to what Shendah responded that he would qualify for the English certificate. To which Mary disagreed with. (Shendah later on verified again and saw that Nigel was very much eligible for the certificate) Shendah stopped the topic of conversation and said that she was going off on a tangent at this point and it was not the matter at hand. Chris laughed. Mary stated that Shawn had the same problem when he was a child about his bowels and that it was normal. She stated she tried soymilk and dairy free diets. She said he was like that as a baby. She then went on the blame Shawn that he was not present in any hospital visit even the day that he was born. To which she started to tear.  Shendah did not bring up the fact that the last hospital visit Shawn was not phoned. Nigel was the one who told Shawn. Shendah acknowledged to her that it must be hard for her to be a single mother but there are some serious concerns such as his hygiene and diet. She claimed that Nigel loves his bath and that he takes one every night. She says his clothes are dirty because he wipes his mouth on them. She claimed he must have missed his bath one time right after hockey. Shendah did not argue not to be confrontational. Shendah strongly recommended for both of them that they do mediation. It would save them time, money, stress and that they would learn to communicate better. Shendah stated once again that they are parents and it is really important that both of them start talking to each other about what is going with Nigel because he is getting worse. Shendah also said to Mary that Shendah did acknowledge that she has been very good about access to Nigel such as changing weekends and bringing him to the States. Shendah said that she knew of mother’s that don’t do that and she appreciated that aspect of her. At this point Shawn walked in the house and Nigel went to play on the computer. Shendah and Chris went outside for a cigarette that Shendah had offered. Chris said he left his cigarettes in the car.', 'Surprise visit from Mary and Chris ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'surprise-visit-from-mary-and-chris', '', '', '2011-02-06 16:59:44', '2011-02-06 21:59:44', '', 0, 'http://shawn-pc/blog/?p=117', 0, 'post', '', 0),
