(163, 1, '2011-01-07 09:30:57', '2011-01-07 14:30:57', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Shawn Thompson</li>\r\n	<li>Other Duty Council (Name unknown)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nShawn waited until the Duty Counsel got in and was free to talk to him. Shawn entered his office and sat down. Shawn gave him all his legal papers (What Shawn served Mary and what Mary served Shawn). Shawn explained what was going on and that he hired Julie Bergeron to represent him but she wasn’t free until the following week. The gentleman said he would try to push the motion to the following week so Shawn would have time to speak with his lawyer. He said that the judge would for sure rule to return Nigel to Mary. Shawn asked him about the affidavit and if he had to serve Mary before the hearing. He told Shawn that he would see to it that the judge would see it.\r\n\r\nHe then left the room without telling Shawn where to go or where to wait.', 'Shawn at the courthouse', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'shawn-at-the-courthouse', '', '', '2011-02-06 21:04:28', '2011-02-07 02:04:28', '', 0, 'http://shawn-pc/blog/?p=163', 0, 'post', '', 0),
