(214, 1, '2011-02-08 19:10:09', '2011-02-09 00:10:09', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Shawn Thompson</li>\r\n	<li>Mary Hyatt</li>\r\n	<li>Nigel Thompson</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMary called Shawn to talk to him about claiming Nigel''s prescriptions on Shawn''s health plan from work. Mary asked Shawn if she could give him receipts from Nigel''s medicine and if Shawn could try to get a refund for them. Mary said that Shawn could put the refund into Nigel''s RESPs. Shawn agreed.\r\n\r\nMary also talked about the court date on February 15 and asked if Shawn was going. Shawn said his lawyer told him he didn''t have to go, so he said he wasn''t going to go. Mary said that her lawyer told Mary that if she wanted to go to mediation that she would have to go to court on that date and have it done, so she thought. Shawn told her that mediation could happen at anytime and that he was willing to go to mediation instead of doing all this though the lawyers. Mary stated that she would want her lawyer to be there but Shawn said he would go to mediation with his lawyer. Mary said that Nigel wanted Shawn to have him for 3 weeks out of 4 per month and that he talked to Shawn already about it. Shawn told him that that was a decision for Mary and Shawn to make and that they will talk about it. Nigel took that as a "NO". Shawn told Mary he would be willing to take Nigel more but that that was something they could talk about in mediation.\r\n\r\nShawn told Mary that he was not looking to take Nigel away from her but that he does want to take part in the decisions that effect Nigel''s well being.\r\n\r\nMary spoke to Shawn about Nigel wiping his mouth on his sleeve and the consequence of him doing that. Mary said she makes him wash his shirt in the sink if she catches him wiping his dirty mouth or nose on his sleeve. Mary asked if Shawn could continue this discipline when Nigel is in his care. Shawn agreed and told her that he thought this was a great idea and that he would like to keep an open communication betw