(225, 1, '2011-02-11 16:00:16', '2011-02-11 21:00:16', 'Shawn called Mary while he was driving to Cornwall to pick up Nigel after his training in Ottawa. Shawn asked Mary what the school had to say about Nigel''s behaviour. Mary said that Nigel was outside when 4 girls held his face in snow and Nigel tried to call for help. Mary said that Nigel then hit the girls to get away from them.  Shawn asked her why Nigel was outside when he wasn''t suppose to be. She said Nigel told her he was outside because of Jonathan, the boy he previously hit. Shawn said that Nigel shouldn''t have been outside and if he would have obeyed, he wouldn''t have gotten into trouble. Mary took Nigel''s side and said that the girls shouldn''t have done what they did. Mary said that in the report from the school there was a lot of detail about the girls'' side of the story and very little about Nigel''s side. Mary stated that the school was on the girls side and against  Nigel. Mary said that the girls hardly got into trouble but Nigel was suspended. Shawn repeated to Mary what Mr. Kennedy told him... that Nigel shouldn''t have been outside and that he was using bad language when he hit the girl(s) and was mad. He said that maybe Nigel wouldn''t haven gotten suspended if he didn''t use foul language.\r\n\r\nMary agreed that Nigel needs to work on his  anger. Shawn said they will ask the school about more details of what happened at their meeting on Wednesday, February 16.', 'Call to Mary on ride to Cornwall', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'call-to-mary-on-ride-to-cornwall', '', '', '2011-02-12 11:08:40', '2011-02-12 16:08:40', '', 0, 'http://shawn-pc/blog/?p=225', 0, 'post', '', 0),
