(250, 1, '2011-02-15 13:00:24', '2011-02-15 18:00:24', 'As per our telephone conversation, here are the details of what happened this morning with Nigel:\r\n \r\nI chatted with Nigel as he came in this morning (9am) - he still seemed to want to talk about what had happened leading up to his suspension yesterday, but was quite ready & willing to go up to class. He assured me he was going to make positive decisions for himself today.\r\n \r\nAfter Nigel went up to class, a staff member came in with an incident report (8:55am): Nigel had been holding a student against the wall, and pushing another student (but Nigel took himself straight in to the office at the belll).\r\n \r\nIn consultation with the principal designate, I decided to monitor the situation to see how his day progressed, rather than calling Nigel right back down to the office and potentially causing him to escalate or setting him off.\r\n \r\nAnother incident report came in from a different staff member at 11:40am: In the SOS room, Nigel had needed to be re-directed many times, and was whiny/confrontational when he was losing the PS2 game. He left SOS yelling at a student, and threatened to kill that student.\r\n \r\nAfter consulting with Mr. Kennedy, we decided that one more incident this afternoon of this severity will result in a suspension.', 'Email from Vice Principle', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'email-from-vice-principle', '', '', '2011-02-15 20:00:55', '2011-02-16 01:00:55', '', 0, 'http://home.plansmash.com/blog/?p=250', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(251, 1, '2011-02-15 20:00:37', '2011-02-16 01:00:37', '', 'Email from Vice Principle', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '250-revision', '', '', '2011-02-15 20:00:37', '2011-02-16 01:00:37', '', 250, 'http://home.plansmash.com/blog/?p=251', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(252, 1, '2011-02-15 18:30:00', '2011-02-15 23:30:00', 'I called Nigel to talk to him about what happened today but no answer so I left a message for him to call me back. (4:30PM)\r\n\r\nMary called me back at 6:30PM.\r\n\r\nMary asked me what time the meeting with Mr. Kennedy was at tomorrow and I told her it was at 9:30AM. She said she thought it was in the afternoon. I asked to speak to Nigel.\r\n\r\nNigel got on the phone and I asked him what happened today. He asked me if I got a phone call too. I ignored his question and repeated mine. He didn''t answer. I told him what he said to that child was very serious. He didn''t say a word. I could hear Mary in the background telling him to listen to what I had to say. I kept repeating that this was very serious. Nigel asked me how many times was I going to repeat that and I told him as many as it takes for him to understand. I told Nigel that I never wanted to hear those words come out of his mouth. I told him that saying those threats will get him "kicked out" of school. I asked him what he got for punishment. He told me that he lost television, Wii and any video games. He said he was still able to play board games and that him and his mother were playing battleship right now. Nigel put me on speaker phone and I told him to take me off because this conversation was only for him and I. Nigel told me it wasn''t my weekend with him so I couldn''t punish him and then said something about Monday being Family Day and that I wasn''t included. I asked to speak to Mary.\r\n\r\nI told Mary that Nigel telling another kid that he was going to kill him was VERY serious and that Nigel could be expelled and even severely punished by law for uttering death threats. That school don''t mess around with that kind of behaviour since the Columbine school Shooting. Mary said that Nigel told her that he didn''t say those words and she was reluctant to respond to that right away... She then said that maybe he did say that because he was very angry. I told her that we would talk about it tomorrow with Mr. Kennedy. I told her I''d see her tomorrow.\r\n\r\nEND OF CALL    ', 'Call to Nigel and Mary about the threat', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'call-to-nigel-and-mary-about-the-threat', '', '', '2011-02-15 20:16:15', '2011-02-16 01:16:15', '', 0, 'http://home.plansmash.com/blog/?p=252', 0, 'post', '', 0);
