(257, 1, '2011-02-16 18:28:14', '2011-02-16 23:28:14', 'I meet with doctor Kirksman about Nigel. She looked very worried about his behaviour and said she would like him to see a psychologist. She said she would like to sit down with Me, Mary and Thomas to discuss this in greater detail. She said that she sent her referral to CHEO and that she thinks there might be a waiting list. She didn''t seem to faun of CHEO. She said children are sent there and they do their assessments and that''s it.\r\n\r\nI told her about the Douglas hospital in Montreal and that I would like Nigel to be assessed there. I explained to her that Shendah works there and has already talked to the children''s psychologist there and said there wouldn''t be a wait. Kirksman said she would like to know more about what they do there and would like to see if they would also follow up on Nigel after they do their assessment. I told her I could get her all the information she needed from Shendah. She asked me to send it to her as soon as possible.\r\n\r\nWe talked about Nigel''s lying to Mary and Mary not believing Nigel would lie to her. I told the doctor that Mary doesn''t think Nigel does anything wrong and that she always takes his side. The doctor agreed that could be the case.\r\n\r\nI asked for a copy of Nigel records and she said she would have to charge me a lot of money. She showed me the guidelines for extra charges that Ontario doctors have to follow. She said she''d have to charge me even if I had a court order.  ', 'Meeting with Dr. Kirtsman', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'meeting-with-dr-kirksman', '', '', '2011-02-18 16:45:56', '2011-02-18 21:45:56', '', 0, 'http://home.plansmash.com/blog/?p=257', 0, 'post', '', 0),
