(267, 1, '2011-02-18 16:44:46', '2011-02-18 21:44:46', 'Shawn,\r\n \r\nI called Mary and thought I would send you an email to give you an update on Nigel''s day (since he refused to bring his agenda home at the end of the day):\r\n \r\nNigel had another difficult day today, but twice managed to turn it around (at least somewhat) with help.\r\n \r\nThis morning, Mrs. Derry called down to the office to say that Nigel was yelling and had thrown a chair (but by the time she was calling down, he was panting loudly and seemed to have started to de-escalate somewhat. We decided to just wait it out and monitor the situation. I checked back in an hour later, and she said he was making a puzzle and seemed calm.\r\n \r\nAt home time, he refused to pack up. I was called to go upstairs because he was out in the hall growling and swearing loudly (F---, F---, F----!) at everyone. The students were shocked at his behaviour, but walked around him as we directed. He refused to bring his agenda home and threatened to tear the page out, and so I suggested he just leave it on the table in his classroom and get it Tuesday when he was ready. His voice was very loud and growly, even gutteral, and he was quite visibly angry, to the point that it worried me to witness this outburst. I offered to help him with his bookbag, and at this point he seemed to be at a lull in his rant, so he let me help him and accompany him down to his bus driver waiting downstairs. He seemed to be starting up again as he left with the driver, although not to the same extent.', 'Email from Central Public School', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'email-from-central-public-school', '', '', '2011-02-18 16:44:46', '2011-02-18 21:44:46', '', 0, 'http://home.plansmash.com/blog/?p=267', 0, 'post', '', 0),
