(75, 1, '2014-02-03 15:43:27', '2014-02-03 15:43:27', '<iframe style="border: 0; width: 350px; height: 470px;" src="http://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/album=1345423249/size=large/bgcol=ffffff/linkcol=63b2cc/tracklist=false/t=1/transparent=true/" height="240" width="320" seamless=""></iframe>\r\n\r\n<em>Well, you know things are going to go well when this happens. Eric and I had been talking for a while about starting a band so decided to go to my studio to see what happens. When trying to start something new it always helps if someone comes to the table with a riff. Eric and I both had something in mind. Oddly enough the two riffs were in the same key and same style. We wrote and recorded the bulk of this in a 3 hour session. Sometimes lightning strikes and it''s nice. Hoping now for lightning to strike twice. </em>\r\n\r\n<em>Sep-7-2013 sessions</em>\r\n<h2>Lyrics</h2>\r\n6:00AM - the alarm clock sings\r\nYour ears still ring from last night''s showBurnt toast - the coffee burns your throat\r\nRush to work\r\nA silk noose that completes the look\r\nof someone else''s résumé\r\nThe fraud you try to sell\r\nRevelations too bitter to face\r\nIn time the noise inside finds a way to seep through your deadened eyes\r\n\r\nTwisting, turning, weeping, let it out\r\nWanting, waiting, yearning, wanna scream it out\r\nBut silent and sleepless, the bed sheets just know what''s up\r\nAt daybreak the brave face hides what knots you up\r\n\r\n6:00AM - the alarm clock stings\r\nYour eyes pour like springs - you fight to stop the flow\r\nA burden binds you to your work\r\nA white shirt, a silk noose, your aging looks\r\nThe tattoo across your chest\r\nthat bleeds onto your sleeves\r\nA bleeding heart repents\r\nThe last words you can''t take back\r\nThat door shuts for good she ain''t coming back\r\n\r\nTwisting, turning, weeping, let it out\r\nWanting, waiting, yearning, wanna scream it out\r\nLonely so lonely, the bed sheets just know what''s up\r\nAt daybreak the brave face hides what knots you up', 'Down to Sound', 'Well, you know things are going to go well when this happens. Eric and I had been talking for a while about starting a band so decided to go to my studio to see what happens. When trying to start something new it always helps if someone comes to the table with a riff. Eric and I both had something in mind. Oddly enough the two riffs were in the same key and same style. We wrote and recorded the bulk of this in a 3 hour session. Sometimes lightning strikes and it''s nice. Hoping now for lightning to strike twice. \r\n\r\nSep-7-2013 sessions', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'down-to-sound', '', '', '2014-02-04 17:02:52', '2014-02-04 17:02:52', '', 0, 'http://plansmash.com/redarms/?p=75', 0, 'post', '', 0);
